#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.39:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Sukhindriyavagga"
msgstr "4. The Pleasure Faculty"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Kaṭṭhopamasutta → araṇi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Kaṭṭhopamasutta"
msgstr "39. The Simile of the Fire Sticks"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties."

msgctxt "sn48.39:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.39:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sukhindriyaṃ, dukkhindriyaṃ, somanassindriyaṃ, domanassindriyaṃ, "
"upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of pleasure, pain, happiness, sadness, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn48.39:1.4"
msgid "Sukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The faculty of pleasure arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as "
"pleasant."

msgctxt "sn48.39:1.5"
msgid "So sukhitova samāno ‘sukhitosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of pleasure, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of pleasure.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:1.6"
msgid ""
"Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ sukhindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, taṃ "
"vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of pleasure ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.212"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:2.1"
msgid "Dukkhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The faculty of pain arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as "
"painful."

msgctxt "sn48.39:2.2"
msgid "So dukkhitova samāno ‘dukkhitosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr "When in a state of pain, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of pain.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva dukkhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"dukkhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, taṃ "
"vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as painful, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of pain ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:3.1"
msgid ""
"Somanassavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati somanassindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The faculty of happiness arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as "
"happiness."

msgctxt "sn48.39:3.2"
msgid "So sumanova samāno ‘sumanosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of happiness, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of happiness.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva somanassavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"somanassavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ somanassindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, "
"taṃ vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as happiness, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of happiness ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:4.1"
msgid ""
"Domanassavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati domanassindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The faculty of sadness arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as "
"sadness."

msgctxt "sn48.39:4.2"
msgid "So dummanova samāno ‘dummanosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of sadness, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of sadness.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva domanassavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"domanassavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ domanassindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, "
"taṃ vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as sadness, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of sadness ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:5.1"
msgid "Upekkhāvedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The faculty of equanimity arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as "
"equanimous."

msgctxt "sn48.39:5.2"
msgid "So upekkhakova samāno ‘upekkhakosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of equanimity, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of "
"equanimity.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva upekkhāvedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"upekkhāvedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannaṃ upekkhindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, taṃ "
"vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as equanimous, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of equanimity ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.213"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā → saṃghaṭanasamodhānā (s1-3, km) | saṃghaṭṭanāsamodhānā (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: nānābhāvāvinikkhepā → nānābhāvanikkhepā (s1-3, km, mr) | nānābhāvā nikkhepā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.39:6.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ kaṭṭhānaṃ saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā usmā jāyati, "
"tejo abhinibbattati; tesaṃyeva kaṭṭhānaṃ nānābhāvāvinikkhepā yā tajjā usmā "
"sā nirujjhati sā vūpasammati;"
msgstr ""
"When you rub two sticks together, heat is generated and fire is produced. "
"But when you part the sticks and lay them aside, any corresponding heat "
"ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn48.39:6.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"sukhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the faculty of pleasure arises dependent on a contact to be "
"experienced as pleasant."

msgctxt "sn48.39:6.3"
msgid "So sukhitova samāno ‘sukhitosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of pleasure, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of pleasure.’"

# Note the shift from uppannam to uppajjati here. This is unusual in a recapitulation. neither BB’s nor my translation reflect this change, and I do not know if it has any significance.
msgctxt "sn48.39:6.4"
msgid ""
"Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, taṃ "
"vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of pleasure ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.39:7.1"
msgid "Dukkhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca … pe …"
msgstr "The faculty of pain …"

msgctxt "sn48.39:7.2"
msgid "somanassavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca … pe …"
msgstr "happiness …"

msgctxt "sn48.39:7.3"
msgid "domanassavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca … pe …"
msgstr "sadness …"

msgctxt "sn48.39:7.4"
msgid "upekkhāvedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati upekkhindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"equanimity arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as equanimous."

msgctxt "sn48.39:7.5"
msgid "So upekkhakova samāno ‘upekkhakosmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When in a state of equanimity, you understand: ‘I’m in a state of "
"equanimity.’"

msgctxt "sn48.39:7.6"
msgid ""
"Tasseva upekkhāvedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā ‘yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"upekkhāvedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati upekkhindriyaṃ taṃ nirujjhati, "
"taṃ vūpasammatī’ti pajānāti”."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as equanimous, you "
"understand that the corresponding faculty of equanimity ceases and stops.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.39:7.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
